29. characters. (1) Laelius-Gaius Laelius, surnamed Sapiens, was born about 186 rac. His father was the friend and associate of the elder Africanus in the Second Punic War, and was elected to the consul· ship, 190 rac. The younger Laelius added broader culture and greater versatility of talent to the good qualities of the elder. He succeeded alike as soldier, orator, and author, and held the offices of tribune, praetor, augur, and consul, the last in the year 140 rao. In the fieres struggle at the capture and destruction of Carthago, he was second in command to Scipio, and displayed remarkable skill and bravery. As a patron of literature he was even more distinguished than in the capacity of statesman or general.
